						<summary>

						<p>Slab in survey No. 283, west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśiva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1482, Raudri, Āshāḍa śu. 12,</hi> corresponding to 1560 A.D., July 4, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It registers a grant of some tolls made by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Koṇḍarājayadēva Mahārāju, son of China Timmaya and grandson of Pedakoṇḍarāju of Āravīḍu for offerings to god Madana Gōpālakṛishṇa of Vēlpucherla (probably the chief installed the god).</p>						

						</summary>
